The article discusses the release of a report by the White House detailing the United States' strategic approach to the People's Republic of China (PRC). The report highlights the need for Americans to understand the nature of the Chinese Communist Party (CCP) and the threats it poses to American interests. It emphasizes the commitment of President Trump and the administration to protect the American people, homeland, and way of life from the CCP's actions and policies. The report outlines a competitive strategy guided by a return to principled realism, as opposed to the failed policies of the past two decades that assumed engagement with rivals would lead to their benign behavior. The full report can be accessed through the provided link.